verses.text_plain: Hear this, all ye people; give ear, all ye inhabitants of the world:
verses.verse_html:
1Hear this, all ye people; give ear, all ye inhabitants of the world: ▼
▼ for: or, of

verses.text_plain: Both low and high, rich and poor, together.
verses.verse_html: 2Both low and high, rich and poor, together.

verses.text_plain: My mouth shall speak of wisdom; and the meditation of my heart shall be of understanding.
verses.verse_html: 3My mouth shall speak of wisdom; and the meditation of my heart shall be of understanding.

verses.text_plain: I will incline mine ear to a parable: I will open my dark saying upon the harp.
verses.verse_html: 4I will incline mine ear to a parable: I will open my dark saying upon the harp.

verses.text_plain: Wherefore should I fear in the days of evil, when the iniquity of my heels shall compass me about?
verses.verse_html: 5Wherefore should I fear in the days of evil, when the iniquity of my heels shall compass me about?

verses.text_plain: They that trust in their wealth, and boast themselves in the multitude of their riches;
verses.verse_html: 6They that trust in their wealth, and boast themselves in the multitude of their riches;

verses.text_plain: None of them can by any means redeem his brother, nor give to God a ransom for him:
verses.verse_html: 7None of them can by any means redeem his brother, nor give to God a ransom for him:

verses.text_plain: (For the redemption of their soul is precious, and it ceaseth for ever:)
verses.verse_html: 8(For the redemption of their soul is precious, and it ceaseth for ever:)

verses.text_plain: That he should still live for ever, and not see corruption.
verses.verse_html: 9That he should still live for ever, and not see corruption.

verses.text_plain: For he seeth that wise men die, likewise the fool and the brutish person perish, and leave their wealth to others.
verses.verse_html: 10For he seeth that wise men die, likewise the fool and the brutish person perish, and leave their wealth to others.

verses.text_plain: Their inward thought is, that their houses shall continue for ever, and their dwelling places to all generations; they call their lands after their own names.
verses.verse_html:
11Their inward thought is, that their houses shall continue for ever, and their dwelling places to all generations; they call their lands after their own names. ▼
▼ all…: Heb. generation and generation

footnotes.body_html: ▼ all…: Heb. generation and generation

verses.text_plain: Nevertheless man being in honour abideth not: he is like the beasts that perish.
verses.verse_html: 12Nevertheless man being in honour abideth not: he is like the beasts that perish.

verses.text_plain: This their way is their folly: yet their posterity approve their sayings. Selah.
verses.verse_html:
13This their way is their folly: yet their posterity approve their sayings. Selah. ▼
▼ approve…: Heb. delight in their mouth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ approve…: Heb. delight in their mouth
footnotes.body_html: ▼ approve…: Heb. delight in their mouth

verses.text_plain: Like sheep they are laid in the grave; death shall feed on them; and the upright shall have dominion over them in the morning; and their beauty shall consume in the grave from their dwelling.
verses.verse_html:
14Like sheep they are laid in the grave; death shall feed on them; and the upright shall have dominion over them in the morning; and their beauty shall consume in the grave from their dwelling. ▼
▼ beauty: or, strength
 , ▼
▼ in the grave from…: or, the grave being an habitation to every one of them

footnotes.body_text: ▼ in the grave from…: or, the grave being an habitation to every one of them
footnotes.body_html: ▼ in the grave from…: or, the grave being an habitation to every one of them

verses.text_plain: But God will redeem my soul from the power of the grave: for he shall receive me. Selah.
verses.verse_html:
15But God will redeem my soul from the power of the grave: for he shall receive me. Selah. ▼
▼ power: Heb. hand
 , ▼
▼ the grave: or, hell

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the grave: or, hell

verses.text_plain: Be not thou afraid when one is made rich, when the glory of his house is increased;
verses.verse_html: 16Be not thou afraid when one is made rich, when the glory of his house is increased;

verses.text_plain: For when he dieth he shall carry nothing away: his glory shall not descend after him.
verses.verse_html: 17For when he dieth he shall carry nothing away: his glory shall not descend after him.

verses.text_plain: Though while he lived he blessed his soul: and men will praise thee, when thou doest well to thyself.
verses.verse_html:
18Though while he lived he blessed his soul: and men will praise thee, when thou doest well to thyself. ▼
▼ while…: Heb. in his life

footnotes.body_html: ▼ while…: Heb. in his life

verses.text_plain: He shall go to the generation of his fathers; they shall never see light.
verses.verse_html:
19He shall go to the generation of his fathers; they shall never see light. ▼
▼ He…: Heb. The soul shall

footnotes.body_html: ▼ He…: Heb. The soul shall

verses.text_plain: Man that is in honour, and understandeth not, is like the beasts that perish.
verses.verse_html: 20Man that is in honour, and understandeth not, is like the beasts that perish.
